.\" heirloom-port-configure(7)
.TH HEIRLOOM-PORT-CONFIGURE 7 "2026-07-02" "Heirloom Darwin port" "Port ALM"
.SH NAME
heirloom-port-configure \- validate environment before build
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B make configure
.br
.B sh scripts/configure.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reports on the host environment and refuses to proceed if any hard
prerequisite is missing. Non-destructive; makes no changes.
.PP
Checks performed:
.PP
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
Host OS + architecture (
.BR sw_vers ,
.BR uname -m ).
.IP \(bu 2
C toolchain: presence and version of
.BR cc ,
.BR make .
.IP \(bu 2
.BR yacc ,
.BR lex
availability (system flex/bison are acceptable; Heirloom devtools versions
are preferred if installed).
.IP \(bu 2
.I /opt/heirloom
existence + writability by the invoking user.
.IP \(bu 2
.I mk.config
prefix declaration (or
.I build/mk.config
for the toolchest).
.IP \(bu 2
Companion Heirloom package presence per
.IR scripts/prereqs-heirloom.txt .
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Environment is ready to build.
.TP
.B >0
One or more hard prerequisites failed; details on stderr.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I scripts/prereqs-heirloom.txt
Companion package check-paths.
.TP
.I mk.config
.TP
.I build/mk.config
Upstream build-configuration file (toolchest).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR heirloom-port-bootstrap (7),
.BR heirloom-port-install (7)
